<br/>

  <p> <strong>Textbooks:</strong> There is no set textbook for this
  course. A good fraction of the material we shall study only resides in
  research papers. There is a good survey by <a
  href="http://www.cs.rutgers.edu/~muthu/">Muthukrishnan</a>, somewhat
  dated at this point, but still very useful for the basics. </p>

  <p> <strong>Course Blog:</strong> Please follow 
  <a href="http://dartstreams.wordpress.com">this weblog</a>
  for updates on all aspects of the course. This is where announcements
  and helpful little notes will be posted from time to time.

  <p> <strong>Lecture Notes:</strong> Here are the <a
  href="Notes/lecnotes.pdf">evolving lecture notes</a> for the course.
  All registered students are required to scribe a minimum of one
  lecture each, and help prepare notes for that lecture, in the style of
  the posted notes. It is imperative to learn basic LaTeX for this
  purpose. We shall regularly update these notes, effectively
  circulating them to all other students. </p>

